From 1fdf0f5291c94f49bf93249ca5987229bb6a0f74 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sam Annazir <sam@corvyx.app>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 23:53:59 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add one-click resume tailoring for a specific job
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- ai.provider.ts: new tailorResume(resume, jobDescription) -> Section[]
  method on the AIProvider interface, implemented in all three adapters
  (openrouter/anthropic/groq) plus delegated through the fallback chain.
- tailorPrompt.ts: single shared system prompt (structure-preservation
  rules apply identically across adapters, so it isn't tripled).
- chatResponseParser.ts: extractBalancedJsonArray + extractTailoredSections,
  same bracket-balanced-scan-past-invalid-candidates approach as the
  existing object extractor, validated against the real SectionSchema.
- ai.routes.ts: POST /api/ai/tailor-resume — loads + migrates the source
  resume (ownership-checked), runs matchJobDescription and tailorResume
  concurrently, and persists the tailored sections as a brand NEW resume
  row (' — Tailored') rather than overwriting the original.
- web/lib/api.ts: aiApi.tailorResume(resumeId, jobDescription).
- New shared TailorResumeModal (resume picker + editable job description
  + AI result with match score/suggestions + link to the new resume),
  used from both:
  - FindJobsPage: 'Tailor Resume' button per card, job description
    pre-filled from the listing.
  - JobTrackerPage: 'Tailor Resume for this Job' button in the
    Edit Application slide-over, job description pre-filled from the
    application's notes (editable either way).
